{"title_page": "Hot Ones", "text_new": "{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Hot Ones\n| image                    = Hot Ones by First We Feast logo.svg\n| genre                    = Interview\n| creator                  = Christopher Schonberger\n| starring                 = [[Sean Evans (interviewer)|Sean Evans]]\n| country                  = [[United States]]\n| language                 = English\n| num_seasons              = 11\n| num_episodes             = 183\n| list_episodes            = \n| network                  = [[YouTube]]\n| picture_format           = [[1080p]] (HD) {{small|(Ep 1\u201348)}}<br/>[[2160p]] (UHD) {{small|(Ep 49\u2013current)}}\n| first_aired              = {{Start date|2015|3|12}}\n| last_aired               = present\n}}\n'''''Hot Ones''''' is a [[YouTube]] [[web series]], created by Christopher Schonberger and produced by [[First We Feast]] and [[Complex (magazine)|Complex Media]]. Its basic premise involves celebrities being interviewed by host [[Sean Evans (interviewer)|Sean Evans]] over a platter of increasingly spicy [[Chicken as food|chicken wings]].\n\n==Format==\nThe format involves Evans and his guests eating ten chicken wings (or an alternative if the guest is [[Veganism|vegan]]), each prepared with a progressively hotter [[hot sauce]]. Evans states the show's [[tagline]] at the beginning of each episode: \"The show with hot questions, and even hotter wings.\"\n\nThe first sauce presented is relatively mild such as [[Sriracha]], which has a rating of 2,200 [[Scoville Scale|Scoville]] units. The final sauce (as of season 4), Hot Ones' own The Last Dab (The Last Dab Reduxx starting in season 6, and The Last Dab XXX starting in Season 10), has a Scoville rating of 2,000,000+.<ref name=\"Scoville Scale\">{{cite web|author=Roberts, Scott|title=Scoville Scale &#8211; The Official Scott Roberts Website |url=http://www.scottrobertsweb.com/scoville-scale |publisher=Scott Roberts Web|accessdate=2017-08-11|date=2012-06-07}}</ref> As per \"tradition\", the guests are encouraged to put a minuscule amount of The Last Dab on the final wing; they are told this is not required, but most guests opt to do so even when already struggling with the heat of the previous wings.\n\nAfter each wing, Evans asks his guest an interview question. As the wings get hotter, the guest typically begins to display the effects of eating the spicier wings and the interview becomes less focused on the guest and more so the struggle to finish the wings. The guests are also provided glasses of water and milk to counteract the effect of the wings.\n\nThe standard show is Evans and one guest eating ten wings each, but in some episodes where there are two guests (such as the episode featuring [[Keegan-Michael Key]] and [[Jordan Peele]]), only five wings are given to each guest. A guest who successfully finishes all ten wings is given the opportunity to promote their upcoming projects. Guests who fail are still afforded this opportunity but are also added to the show's Hall of Shame.\n\n== Show history ==\nThe show was created by First We Feast Founder Christopher Schonberger. Schonberger cites [[Alexa Chung]]'s quirky interview show ''[[Popworld]]'' as the inspiration for the show.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/celebs-will-say-anything-if-you-blast-them-with-hot-sauce-1522157082|title=Celebs Will Say Anything if You Blast Them With Hot Sauce|last=Steinberg|first=Don|date=2018-03-27|work=Wall Street Journal|access-date=2018-03-27|language=en-US|issn=0099-9660}}</ref> The show is hosted by Sean Evans.\n\n==List of episodes==\n\n=== Season 1 ===\n{{Episode table |background=#FFA6B9|overall= |season= |title= |airdate= |episodes=\n\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 1\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 1\n| Title           = [[Tony Yayo]] Talks Shmoney Dance and Eminem's Taco Habit While Eating Spicy Wings\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2015|3|12}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = FFA6B9\n}}\n{{Episode 