and]], served as [[Chaplain of the United States Senate]] (1810\u20131811).\n* [[Will Addison]] (born 1992), English rugby union player\n* [[William Addison (disambiguation)]]\n* [[Viscount Addison]]:\n** [[Christopher Addison, 1st Viscount Addison]] (1869\u20131951), British politician\n** [[Christopher Addison, 2nd Viscount Addison]] (1904\u20131976), British engineer\n** [[Michael Addison, 3rd Viscount Addison]] (1914\u20131992), British soldier and educator\n** [[William Addison, 4th Viscount Addison]] (born 1945), British peer\n\n== Nickname ==\n* [[Henry Mackenzie]] (1745\u20131831), Scottish novelist and miscellaneous writer, known by the [[sobriquet]] \"Addison of the North\"\n\n== Fictional characters ==\n* Addison DeWitt, a character in the film ''[[All About Eve]]''\n* [[List of Saw characters#Addison|Addison]], a character from the American film ''Saw II''\n* [[Addison Montgomery]], character in ''Grey's Anatomy'' and ''Private Practice''\n* Addison Schach, a character in the film \"November Criminals\"\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{given name}}\n\n{{surname|Addison}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Addison}}\n[[Category:Patronymic surnames]]\n[[Category:Surnames of Lowland Scottish origin]]\n[[Category:English masculine given names]]\n[[Category:English feminine given names]]\n[[Category:English unisex given names]]\n[[Category:Given names originating from a surname]]\n", "text_old": "{{Other uses|Addison (disambiguation){{!}}Addison}}\n'''Addison''' is an [[Old English]] [[given name]] whose etymological meaning is \"son of Adam.\"<ref name=\"Hanks Coates McClure 2016\">{{cite book\n| last        = Hanks\n| first       = P.\n| last2       = Coates\n| first2      = R.\n| last3       = McClure\n| first3      = P.\n| title       = The Oxford Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland\n| publisher   = OUP Oxford\n| year        = 2016\n| isbn        = 978-0-19-252747-9\n| url         = https://books.google.com/books?id=0AyDDQAAQBAJ&pg=PA14\n| access-date = 