{"title_page": "1924 Birthday Honours", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=February 2016}}\nThe '''1924 Birthday Honours''' were appointments by King [[George V]] to [[Orders, decorations, and medals of the United Kingdom|various orders and honours]] to reward and highlight good works by citizens of the British Empire. The appointments were made to celebrate the [[Queen's Official Birthday|official birthday]] of The King, and were published in ''[[The London Gazette]]'' on 3 June 1924.<ref>{{London Gazette |issue=32941 |supp=y |pages=4407\u20134422 |date=3 June 1924}}</ref>\n\nThe recipients of honours are displayed here as they were styled before their new honour, and arranged by honour, with classes (Knight, Knight Grand Cross, ''etc.'') and then divisions (Military, Civil, ''etc.'') as appropriate.\n\n==United Kingdom and British Empire==\n\n===[[Privy Council of the United Kingdom|Privy Councillor]]===\nThe King appointed the following to His Majesty's Most Honourable Privy Council:\n*[[T. P. O'Connor|Thomas Power O'Connor]] {{post-nominals|country=GBR|MA|MP}} For political services\n\n===[[Baronet]]cies===\n*[[Sir Alexander Grant, 1st Baronet|Alexander Grant]], Chairman of the firm of [[McVitie's|McVittie and Price]]. For public services. \n*Sir [[Humphry Rolleston|Humphry Davy Rolleston]] {{post-nominals|country=GBR|KCB|MA|MD|DCL|LLD}} President of the [[Royal College of Physicians]]\n\n===[[Knight Bachelor]]===\n*Gerald Bellhouse {{post-nominals|country=GBR|CBE}} Chief Inspector of Factories, Home Office\n*[[David Young Cameron]] {{post-nominals|country=GBR|RA|LLD}} In recognition of his contributions to Art\n*Richard Davies {{post-nominals|country=GBR|CBE|JP}} Deputy, Alderman and Chief Commoner, Corporation, of London\n*[[William Galloway (mining engineer)|William Galloway]] {{post-nominals|country=GBR|DSc}} For public services\n*Benjamin Hawkins, Solicitor to the Board of Customs and Excise\n*Fred Hiam, For public services\n*George Anthony King {{post-nominals|country=GBR|MA}} Chief Master, Supreme Court Taxing Office\n*Charles Mendl, For services to His Majesty's Embassy, Paris\n*Harold George Parlett {{post-nominals|country=GBR|CMG}} Japanese Counsellor of His Majesty's Embassy, Tokyo\n*The Rt. Hon. [[William Lowrie Sleigh]] {{post-nominals|country=GBR|JP|DL}} [[Lord Provost of Edinburgh]]\n*Alderman John Utting {{post-nominals|country=GBR|JP|DL|MECS|LECP}} Chairman of Finance Committee, Liverpool Corporation. [[Lord Mayor of Liverpool]], 1917\u201318\n*[[Sir Ralph Wedgwood, 1st Baronet|Ralph Lewis Wedgwood]] {{post-nominals|country=GBR|CB|CMG}} General Manager, [[London and North Eastern Railway]]\n*[[Arthur Smith Woodward]] {{post-nominals|country=GBR|LLD|FES}} lately Keeper of Geology in the [[British Museum]]\n\n;British India\n*Provash Chandra Mitter {{post-nominals|country=GBR|CIE}} Vakil, High Court, Calcutta, Bengal, late Minister, Government of Bengal\n*Justice Victor [[Murray Coutts-Trotter]], Chief Justice, [[Madras High Court]],\n*Justice [[Babington Bennett Newbould]], Indian Civil Service, Puisne Judge, High Court, Calcutta, Bengal\n*Justice Henry Scott-Smith, Indian Civil Service, Puisne Judge, High Court, Lahore, Punjab\n*Justice Theodore Garo Piggott, Indian Civil Service, Puisne Judge, High Court, Allahabad, United Provinces\n*[[Montagu Sherard Dawes Butler]] {{post-nominals|country=GBR|CB|CIE|CVO|CBE}} Indian Civil Service, Secretary to the Government of India in the Department of Education, Health and Lands\n*[[Peter Clutterbuck|Peter Henry Clutterbuck]] {{post-nominals|country=GBR|CIE|OBE|VD}} Inspector-General of Forests\n*[[Gilbert Walker|Gilbert Thomas Walker]] {{post-nominals|country=GBR|CSI|DSc|PhD|FES}} Director-General of Observatories in India\n*Lieutenant-Colonel Thomas John Carey-Evans {{post-nominals|country=GBR|MC}} Indian Medical Service, Surgeon to His Excellency The Viceroy\n*Alexander James Anderson {{post-nominals|country=GBR|CSI|VD}} 